President Obama has nominated Corinne Ann Beckwith to be an appellate judge for the District of Columbia Court of Appeals. Beckwith has been an attorney in the Appellate Division of the Public Defender Service for the District of Columbia since 1999 and has been a supervisor in that office since 2009. She has previously worked as an appellate attorney at Michigan's State Appellate Defender Office and taught criminal appellate practice at Wayne State University Law School. Beckwith has a Bachelor of Arts degree in English from Kalamazoo College, a Master of Science degree in journalism from the University of Illinois, and a law degree from the University of Michigan Law School, where she served as editor-in-chief of the Michigan Law Review. She has also served as a law clerk to Judge Richard D. Cudahy on the United States Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit and to Associate Justice John Paul Stevens on the Supreme Court of the United States. President Obama expressed confidence in Beckwith's ability, integrity, and independence in nominating her for the position.